          "text": "Base directory for this skill: /Users/karthikp/.claude/plugins/cache/pageup/pageup-tools/1.3.12/skills/coder-workspace-troubleshoot\n\n# Coder CDE Troubleshooting (PageUp)\n\nBattle-tested diagnosis paths for the PageUp Coder deployment. Each failure mode below was hit and fixed at least once; the \"Why\" explains the underlying mechanism so you can adapt when the symptom mutates.\n\n> **Staleness warning:** Infrastructure facts here are point-in-time (secret IDs, upstream bug status, image pins). Confirm with a live check before asserting a fact as current — especially anything marked ⏳.\n\n## Environment facts\n\n- Coder server: `https://coder.pageupinternal.cloud`, running on AKS cluster `coderdev-aks` (resource group `coderdev-rg`, Azure).\n- The cluster uses a **classic service principal** (clientId `ada40b38-65a0-4924-b53c-3113f6459edb`, display name `aks--coder-sp-name`), *not* managed identity. Its secret expires every 365 days (see §1).\n- Each workspace gets its own namespace: `coder-<workspace-name>`.\n- Coder uses the **built-in provisioner** inside the coder server pod (no external provisionerDaemon). It has no git credentials by default (see §6).\n- Templates live in the **platform-tools** repo under `coder/templates/` (claude-code-bmad, flexible-forms, monolith-*, etc.). Pushing a template affects everyone who creates a workspace afterwards; existing workspaces are untouched unless `template_require_active_version` is enabled.\n- Private images come from `ghcr.io/pageuppeopleorg/...` and pull via an `imagePullSecrets` named `github-pat`, propagated into workspace namespaces by **emberstack reflector** from source secret `coder/github-pat` (see §3).\n\n## Triage: route by symptom\n\nRun the basics first — they disambiguate most cases in one shot:\n\n```sh\ncoder show <workspace>                                   # build status, params, per-agent health\nkubectl get pods -n coder-<workspace>\nkubectl get events -n coder-<workspace> --sort-by=.lastTimestamp | tail -20\n```\n\n| What you see | Go to |\n|---|---|\n| PVCs stuck `Pending`, workspaces hang with no pod events, CSI 401 errors | §1 AKS service principal expiry |\n| Agents time out at 120s `connection_timeout`, pods `ImagePullBackOff` on ghcr images | §2 → §3 |\n| LocalStack agent has `start_error`, logs say \"License activation failed\" | §4 LocalStack license |\n| `claude` asks for `/login` or shows onboarding in a fresh workspace | §5 OAuth token wiring |\n| coder CLI: `x509: certificate has expired or is not yet valid` | §7 TLS cert |\n| Template build fails at `terraform init` fetching a `git::` module | §6 Provisioner git auth |\n| `coder template push` says \"Terraform initialized in an empty directory\" | §8 Template push |\n| Browser shows \"Invalid Host header\" on a workspace preview URL | §9 webpack allowedHosts |\n| Claude Desktop SSH / Coder Connect can't reach a workspace | §10 Client-side connectivity |\n| Windows agent (monolith-*) stuck `timeout` while sibling Linux agents connected; pod Running | §11 Stalled Windows agent download |\n\nMultiple symptoms can stack (e.g. the flexible-forms validation hit §3 *and* §4 simultaneously). Fix the cheapest one first, rebuild, re-observe.\n\n## §1 Workspaces stuck Pending — AKS service principal expiry\n\n**Symptom:** Every PVC stuck `Pending`; new workspaces hang in `Pending` with no pod events; the Coder server itself stays up (it doesn't talk to ARM). VolumeAttachments accumulate with `attached=false`.\n\n**Confirm:**\n```sh\nkubectl describe pvc -n coder-<workspace>\n```\nLook for CSI controller event: `ClientSecretCredential authentication failed … RESPONSE 401: invalid_client`. Check the 401 **first** — dangling VolumeAttachments are a downstream symptom, don't chase them.\n\n**Why:** The cluster was bootstrapped with `az ad sp create-for-rbac` (default secret expiry 365 days) and has `identity: null`. When the SP secret expires, every disk operation (attach, detach, provision) fails silently from Coder's perspective.\n\n**Fix:**\n```sh\naz ad sp credential reset --id ada40b38-65a0-4924-b53c-3113f6459edb --years 2\naz aks update-credentials -g coderdev-rg -n coderdev-aks --reset-service-principal \\\n  --service-principal ada40b38-65a0-4924-b53c-3113f6459edb --client-secret <new-secret>\n```\nThen update the Bitwarden entry `AZ Deployment secrets`. Long-term fix: migrate to managed identity (`az aks update … --enable-managed-identity`) so this stops recurring annually.\n\n## §2 Agents time out at 120s connection_timeout\n\n**Symptom:** `coder show` reports agents (e.g. `main`, `postgres`) as timed out; terraform apply itself succeeded.\n\nThis is almost never the agent's fault — the pod never got far enough to start it. Check pod state:\n\n```sh\nkubectl get pods -n coder-<workspace>\n```\n\n- `ImagePullBackOff` on `ghcr.io/pageuppeopleorg/...` → §3 (missing `github-pat` secret).\n- Pulling a huge image (e.g. .NET workbench) that legitimately exceeds 120s → consider raising `connection_timeout` in the template or setting `image_pull_policy = \"IfNotPresent\"` so cached images are reused on rebuild.\n- Pod `Pending` with no events → §1.\n\n## §3 ImagePullBackOff — github-pat secret missing from new namespace\n\n**Symptom:** Private ghcr images won't pull in a freshly created workspace namespace; the same template worked for an older workspace.\n\n**Confirm:**\n```sh\nkubectl get secret github-pat -n coder-<workspace>   # NotFound = this issue\n```\n\n**Why:** No template creates `github-pat` — they all assume it exists. The emberstack **reflector** copies it from `coder/github-pat` into namespaces on a **fixed hourly cycle (runs at HH:16:41 UTC)**, not on namespace-creation events. A workspace created just after the cycle waits up to ~1h, plus k8s image-pull backoff (~5 min cap), before recovering on its own.\n\n**Fix (fast path)** — manually copy the secret; the reflector does exactly this, so it's safe:\n```sh\nkubectl get secret github-pat -n coder -o yaml | sed 's/namespace: coder/namespace: coder-<workspace>/' | kubectl apply -f -\n```\nPods then recover on the next image-pull retry (≤5 min). Or just wait for the next HH:16:41 cycle.\n\n**Security note:** the `coder/github-pat` secret has leaked its decoded PAT into the `last-applied-configuration` annotation before. If you touch it, prefer `kubectl create` over `kubectl apply -f`, and consider rotating.\n\n## §4 LocalStack fails license activation (exit code 55)\n\n**Symptom:** LocalStack agent connects but reports `start_error`; container logs show `License activation failed: No credentials were found … set the LOCALSTACK_AUTH_TOKEN`.\n\n**Why:** `localstack/localstack:latest` silently became a **Pro** image requiring a license token. Templates that pinned nothing broke when the tag moved. The community image is `localstack/localstack-community:latest`.\n\n**Fix:** Pin the image in the template (e.g. `coder/templates/flexible-forms/variables.tf`):\n```hcl\nimage = \"localstack/localstack:2.3.2\"          # or localstack/localstack-community:latest\n```\n⏳ A `2.3.2` pin was **pushed to the Coder server** in May 2026 but never committed back to the repo — `variables.tf` in git may still say `latest` (confirmed drifted as of June 2026). Check *both* the repo file and the active template version, and commit the pin so the next `template push` from the repo doesn't silently regress it (see §8 Symptom C). Alternative (if Pro is actually wanted): wire `LOCALSTACK_AUTH_TOKEN` into the container env + a workspace parameter.\n\n## §5 claude asks for /login in a fresh claude-code-bmad workspace\n\n**Symptom:** User created the workspace, supplied (or believes they supplied) an OAuth token, but `claude` shows the onboarding/login screen.\n\n**Diagnose in this order** (inside the workspace terminal):\n```sh\necho \"OAUTH_LEN=${#CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN}\"; echo \"OAUTH_PREFIX=${CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN:0:8}\"\ntest -f ~/.claude.json && jq '{hasCompletedOnboarding}' ~/.claude.json; ls -la ~/.claude/\n```\n\n- **`OAUTH_LEN=0`** → the env var never reached the shell. The most common cause (seen in practice): the `Claude OAuth Token` workspace parameter was simply never filled in at creation. Verify with `coder show <workspace>` — check the `claude_oauth_token` parameter. The Coder form is a plain text input that doesn't echo back, so an empty paste goes unnoticed.\n- **`OAUTH_LEN` ~100+** but still prompting → distinguish *what* it shows: onboarding screen (seed missing) vs \"Invalid API key\" (token bad — re-run `claude setup-token` locally and rebuild). Also check `~/.claude/.credentials.json` from a previous session overriding the env var.\n\n**Key mechanics:**\n- The fix that seeds `~/.claude.json` lives in `coder/templates/claude-code-bmad/modules.tf` `post_install_script` (PR #150). `post_install_script` runs **only on first install** — restarting an existing workspace will not re-run it. **Rebuild** (or create fresh), don't restart.\n- Token generation: user runs `claude setup-token` on their own machine, pastes the output into the `Claude OAuth Token` parameter at workspace creation.\n- Quick unblock for an existing workspace without rebuilding:\n  ```sh\n  export CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=\"<setup-token output>\"\n  claude\n  ```\n- Shells matter: `coder_env` injects into the **agent's** environment. Coder web terminals inherit it; detached tmux or odd SSH paths may not.\n\n## §6 terraform init fails fetching a private module — provisioner git auth\n\n**Symptom:** Template push or workspace build fails during `terraform init` with a git auth error on a `module { source = \"git::https://github.com/PageUpPeopleOrg/...\" }`.\n\n**Why:** The **built-in provisioner** (inside the coder server pod) fetches modules — not the workspace agent. It has no git credentials: `coder-values.yaml` ships `volumes: []` / `volumeMounts: []`, and `CODER_EXTERNAL_AUTH_0` is workspace-facing OAuth, invisible to the provisioner.\n\n**The tempting shortcut does NOT work:** the org-wide `github-pat` secret is type `kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson` (image-pull format git can't consume) and is scoped for package reads, not repo contents.\n\n**Fix (Coder's documented pattern):**\n1. Create a fine-grained PAT — read-only Contents on just the module repo(s).\n2. Create a `git-secrets` Opaque secret holding a `.gitconfig` + `.git-credentials` pair.\n3. Mount at `/home/coder/.gitconfig` and `/home/coder/.git-credentials` via `coder.volumes` / `coder.volumeMounts` in `coder-values.yaml` (pod runs non-root uid 1000, HOME=/home/coder).\n4. `helm upgrade`. The Coder image already includes git — no image change needed.\n\n## §7 coder CLI TLS errors\n\n**Symptom:** `tls: failed to verify certificate: x509: certificate has expired or is not yet valid` from any coder CLI call.\n\n**Confirm + fix:** Check the actual cert on the ingress:\n```sh\nopenssl s_client -connect coder.pageupinternal.cloud:443 -servername coder.pageupinternal.cloud </dev/null 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -dates\n```\nIf expired, inspect how the cert is issued (cert-manager / ingress annotations in the coder namespace on `coderdev-aks`) and renew there. Also sanity-check the client clock — \"not yet valid\" on one machine only is usually local clock skew.\n\n## §8 coder template push problems\n\n**Symptom A — empty upload:** push logs show `Terraform initialized in an empty directory!` then `Error: No configuration files`. The tar reached the server empty.\n\n**Fix:** Don't rely on `cd` (especially in compound commands / PowerShell). Run from the platform-tools repo root with an explicit directory:\n```sh\ncoder template push <template-name> --yes -d ./coder/templates/<template-name> --message \"...\"\n```\n\n**Symptom B — nothing changed after push:** remember version semantics — a push creates a new **active version** affecting only workspaces created afterwards. To validate, **rebuild** an existing workspace against the new version or