            "channel_id": "C047GLM65T3",
            "message": "Here are the two `devspace.yaml` files that drive this example 👇\n\n**`mock-conductor/devspace.yaml`** — the root repo:\n```yaml\nname: mock-conductor\nversion: v1\nimage:\n  dockerfile: Dockerfile\n  context: .\ndependencies:\n  - name: mock-ai-stack\n    source:\n      git: https://github.com/humblelistener/mock-ai-stack.git\n      branch: main\n    vars:\n      - name: PORT\n        value: \"8080\"\ndev:\n  ports:\n    - port: 3000\n      name: app\n      app: true          # -> creates the coder_app button\n  env:\n    - name: DB_ENDPOINT\n      value: postgres://conductor:conductor@postgres:5432/conductor?sslmode=disable\n    - name: AI_ENDPOINT\n      value: http://mock-ai-stack:8080\n  command: [\"go\", \"run\", \".\"]\n```\n\n**`mock-ai-stack/devspace.yaml`** — the dependency repo:\n```yaml\nname: mock-ai-stack\nversion: v1\nimage:\n  dockerfile: Dockerfile\n  context: .\ndev:\n  ports:\n    - port: 8080\n      name: api\n      app: true\n  env:\n    - name: PORT\n      value: \"8080\"\n```\n\n**How the CLI reads it:**\n• `name` → becomes the k8s Service/deployment name. That's *why* `AI_ENDPOINT: http://mock-ai-stack:8080` resolves — the hostname matches the dependency's `name`.\n• `dependencies[]` → each is another repo (by `git` URL). The CLI clones it, reads *its* devspace.yaml, and gives it its own pod + Service. `mock-conductor` → depends on → `mock-ai-stack`.\n• `dev.ports` → container ports exposed as Services; `app: true` also renders the clickable Coder app (the :3000 one on the DNS URL above).\n• `dev.env` → env injected into the pod; cross-service URLs just use the other service's `name` as the host.\n• Backing services like **postgres** aren't in devspace.yaml — they come from the root's `docker-compose.yml`, and the CLI merges both graphs into one template.\n\nNet: the root declares its ports/env + lists cross-repo deps; each dep declares its own. The CLI walks that graph and emits a single Coder template that runs everything together.",
